author: Cybernews
description:
In this episode of Private Chat by Cybernews, we will be talking with Michiel Prins, one of the co-founders and the head of product at HackerOne. He discusses the company's origins, explaining it was created to solve the problem he and his co-founder faced as pen testers. There was no safe or reliable way to report vulnerabilities they found to the companies that could fix them. Michiel Prins also covers the platform's evolution from a simple "security at inbox" to a major bug bounty system and shares his vision for the "bionic" future of hacking, where AI augments human creativity.
